{"title":"Shiny and Chrome","link":"https://kottke.org/24/10/shiny-and-chrome","date":1727900703000,"content":"\n        <p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-01.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-01.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-01.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"795\" alt=\"Chrome logo that says 'Capri'\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-02.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-02.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-02.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"857\" alt=\"Chrome logo that says 'Desoto'\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-03.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-03.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-03.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"798\" alt=\"Chrome logo that says 'Volvo'\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-04.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-04.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-04.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"526\" alt=\"Chrome logo that says 'Courier'\" /></p>\n\n<p><img src=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-05.jpg\" srcset=\"/cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=500,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-05.jpg 500w, /cdn-cgi/image/format=auto,fit=scale-down,width=1200,metadata=none/plus/misc/images/chrome-logos-05.jpg 1200w\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1200\" height=\"900\" alt=\"Chrome logo that says 'Avanti II'\" /></p>\n\n<p>A site called <a href=\"https://chromeography.com/\">Chromeography</a> collects chrome logos and typography from vintage cars &amp; electric appliances. As I was looking through these, I wondered: â€œWhat the hell is chrome anyway?â€ So I <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chrome_plating\">looked it up</a>:</p>\n\n<blockquote><p>Chrome plating (less commonly chromium plating) is a technique of electroplating a thin layer of chromium onto a metal object. A chrome plated part is called chrome, or is said to have been chromed. The chromium layer can be decorative, provide corrosion resistance, facilitate cleaning, and increase surface hardness. Sometimes, a less expensive substitute for chrome, such as nickel may be used for aesthetic purposes.</p></blockquote>\n\n<p>(via <a href=\"https://www.threads.net/@presentandcorrect/post/DAVhwZOtTb3\">@presentandcorrect</a>)</p>\n\n        \n\n         <p><strong>Tags:</strong> <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/cars\">cars</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/design\">design</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/logos\">logos</a> Â· <a href=\"https://kottke.org/tag/typography\">typography</a></p>\n\n         <p>ğŸ’¬ <a href=\"https://kottke.org/24/10/shiny-and-chrome\">Join the discussion on kottke.org</a> â†’</p>\n\n    ","author":"Jason Kottke","siteTitle":"Kottke","siteHash":"89a883271b4598f9b33ebe87be70d38557bcd266e68aee521a8f93622e0ab723","entryHash":"ec21826fddd3901a712bbedd2fa07c60371b1ec8668b87a3a69160eb320a57cc","category":"Sites"}